A table where duplicate rows are not permitted.

The trigger defines events that happen when some other event called a triggering event occurs. This database object is essentially a stored SQL statement associated with a table called a subject table.

The term Teradata Columnar describes tables with a Primary Index (PI) Primary AMP Index (PA) or No Primary Index (NoPI) that are column-partitioned. It is a physical database design implementation that consists of an integrated set of options that support column partitioning columnar storage autocompression and other capabilities that you can specify for column-partitioned tables.
Column-partitioned tables and join indexes can have a Primary Index method

Queries can contain Named Parameters making it easy to reuse a query because the only changes are the data values (for example in a Where clause). Named Parameters function like variables. Enter the value for a named parameter once. If it is used in multiple places within the query the same value is used in all places.
Represents a large binary string of raw bytes. A binary large object (BLOB) column can store binary objects such as graphics video clips files and documents.
Represents a large character string. A character large object (CLOB) column can store character data such as simple text or HTML.
The UDT data type represents a custom data type for modeling the structure and behavior of real-world entities used by applications.
XML data type that allows you to store XML content in a compact binary form that preserves the information set of the XML document
A UDT (user defined data type) that is based on a single predefined data type such as INTEGER or VARCHAR.
A user defined data type (UDT) with a collection of one or more fields called attributes where each attribute is defined as a predefined data type or other UDT

Support to Teradata Database for three dimensional geospatial coordinate data. The feature includes a geospatial data type minimum bounding box (MBB)that adds z-coordinate support to existing geospatial methods and adds new methods specific to three dimensional data.
A data type that represents a numeric value with optional precision and scale limitations.

Called Persistent Stored Modules in the ANSI/ISO SQL:2008 standard. They are written in SQL and consist of a set of control and condition handling statements that make SQL a computationally complete programming language. These features provide a server-based procedural interface to the database for application programmers. Teradata stored procedure facilities are a subset of and conform to the ANSI/ISO SQL:2008 standards for semantics.
UDFs allow you to extend SQL by writing your own functions.

A table function is invoked in the FROM clause of an SQL SELECT statement and returns a table a row at a time in a loop to the SELECT statement. The function can produce the rows of a table from the input arguments passed to it or by reading an external file or message queue.

You can create user-defined table operators which accept one or more tables or table expressions as input and generate a table as output. A table operator is a form of UDF that can only be specified in the FROM clause of a SELECT statement.
The ability to run functions on a foreign server. The output of the HELP FOREIGN FUNCTION command shows detailed information about the ML Engine function specified.
Provides a way to use remote data source rather than the Teradata Database to process queries involving remote tables.
